Step 1. Prepare Asset Paths in Google Earth Engine

Before running the scripts, create dedicated asset folders in your GEE account for storing intermediate and final outputs.

You need to define four separate asset paths:

Geographical feature data
(e.g., static spatial predictors such as latitude, longitude, DEM, etc.)

Sentinel-3 (S3) processed data

Vegetation feature data

SIF reference / intermediate data

Each category should have its own GEE asset path.
Example structure:

users/your_username/ProjectName/Geo_features/
users/your_username/ProjectName/S3_processed/
users/your_username/ProjectName/Vegetation_features/
users/your_username/ProjectName/SIF_data/

Make sure all paths are correctly defined in the corresponding scripts before execution.

Step 2. Download my_eogpr

Download the trained my_eogpr model from this repository (or the provided source).

Place it in your working environment.

Before running the GPR prediction step, ensure that:

my_eogpr is properly imported

All dependencies are installed

The model file is accessible from your runtime environment

Step 3. Run the Preprocessing and Prediction Scripts

Run the following scripts in order:

3.1 Run Geo_features_function

This script generates geographical feature data and exports it to the predefined GEE asset path.

At this stage, you can configure:

Time range

Spatial extent

Spatial resolution

3.2 Run S3_process

This script processes Sentinel-3 OLCI data and exports the results to the S3 asset path defined in Step 1.

You can also configure:

Start and end dates

Study region

Output resolution

3.3 Run RunPyeogpr

Before executing this script:

Load the my_eogpr model into the environment.

This script:

Loads the previously generated features

Applies the Gaussian Process Regression (GPR) model

Exports the prediction results to the specified asset path

Ensure that all input asset paths are correctly set.

Step 4. Generate Final SIF Output

Finally, run:

Step_4_SIF_output

This script:

Loads all intermediate assets generated in previous steps

Produces the final SIF dataset

Exports the SIF results to the asset path defined in Step 1

The output SIF data will be stored in your designated GEE asset folder.

Workflow Summary

Create asset paths in GEE

Download and prepare my_eogpr

Run:

Geo_features_function

S3_process

RunPyeogpr (after loading my_eogpr)

Run Step_4_SIF_output to generate final SIF products

Notes

All parameters (time range, region, resolution) can be configured inside the scripts.

Ensure consistent projection and resolution across all steps.

Verify that all asset paths exist before running exports.

Large-scale processing may require batching by date or region.
